	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading mw-first-heading"><span class="mw-page-title-namespace">Wikisource</span><span class="mw-page-title-separator">:</span><span class="mw-page-title-main">Manual of Style</span></h1>
	<div id="bodyContent" class="vector-body">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikisource</div>
		<div id="contentSub"><div id="mw-content-subtitle"></div></div>
		<div id="contentSub2"></div>
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#searchInput">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><p>The purpose of this page is to outline standards for the presentation of various pages.  In many cases there are options available.  Choosing one of those options does not mean that the other options are necessarily wrong.
</p><p>If a subject below gets too long it can be moved to its own Wikisource:MOS page.  For now please add style topics where you feel decisions will be needed.
</p>
